article_metadata.description: I read with interest and dismay two contrasting articles concerning UnitedHealth in Wednesday's Dispatch Business section. The Associated Press article “UnitedHealth to trim ACA (Affordable Care Act) exchanges to handful of states” also featured as a “teaser” that said the company will “slash its participation in the Affordable Care Act’s insurance exchanges” because “nonprofit health insurance cooperatives created by the ACA have reported deep 2015 losses.”
